.SH NAME
\fB²DPROG² \- Duty roster anomalies\fR: compares the duty roster with actual practice records and reports discrepancies as an HTML report
.br
(manpage-Hilfe in deutsch verfügbar: 'man ²DPROG²' oder 'man -Lde ²DPROG²')
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fB²DPROG² [-<shortopt>|--<longopt> [<supplement>]] ...\fR
.SH SHORT DESCRIPTION
\fB²DPROG²\fR is a command line program that compares, for each staff member, the planned duty (tables \fBdienstplan\fR/\fBwochenplan\fR) of the last 21 days with the actual number of practice records (table \fBquelle.eintraege\fR) they created on that day.
.br
Days are flagged where the roster says the staff member should have worked but few or no records exist, and conversely days where the roster says they were off but records were nevertheless created.
.br
For each staff member with anomalies, a line with date, planned and actual duty code, target hours, hit count and, if applicable, the latest changes to the roster entry is output.
.br
The result is written as an HTML file \fBDienstplanauffaelligkeiten_<date>.html\fR into the directory \fB/DATA/Patientendokumente\fR.
.SH INSTALLATION
.br
First, please read the chapters 'Functionality', 'Preconditions', 'Automatically installed software packages' and 'Implications' below. Then, if connected to the internet, call (e.g. by copying the line and pasting it into a terminal):
.br
\fBN=²DPROG²;P=${N}_inst.sh;cd ~;wget https://raw.githubusercontent.com/²gitv²/$N/master/install.sh -O$P&&sh $P\fR
.br
At last, call:
.br
 \fB²DPROG²\fR
.br
and answer some questions of the program.
.SH USAGE
Ideally, the program should have installed itself after the first call(s) and one-time answering of some questions in a self-running way.
.br
The program is typically called periodically via \fBcron\fR (option \fB-cm\fR/\fB--cronminutes\fR). At each call the HTML report is regenerated (or overwritten for the current day) and file/directory permissions are set so it stays readable and updatable across the practice network.
.br
Staff members with the code \fBnotiz\fR as well as the permanently excluded codes (currently \fBgs\fR, \fBtk\fR) are not evaluated; nor are staff members whose date of leaving lies more than 21 days in the past.
