.SH FUNCTIONALITY
.LP
When called, '\fB²DPROG²\fR' accomplishes the following:
.LP
\fB1)\fR General and program-specific defaults are set.
.LP
\fB2)\fR Defaults are loaded from the configuration file, if it exists (default: \fB²DPROG².conf\fR in the same directory as \fB²DPROG²\fR, default: \fB/usr/local/sbin/²DPROG²\fR).
.LP
\fB3)\fR Command line arguments are evaluated and override the configuration file where applicable.
.LP
\fB4)\fR Questions are asked if values are missing or an interactive option is set.
.LP
\fB5)\fR The program inserts itself if wanted and necessary into root's \fBcrontab\fR in order to be called in adjustable intervals.
.LP
\fB6)\fR The MariaDB database is initialised.
.LP
\fB7)\fR All active staff members are read from the table \fBmitarbeiter\fR (excluded: codes \fBnotiz\fR, \fBgs\fR, \fBtk\fR, and those who left more than 21 days ago).
.LP
\fB8)\fR For each staff member, the last 21 days are checked individually:
.br
\fBa)\fR The planned duty for the day is determined from \fBwochenplan\fR (default per weekday) or \fBdienstplan\fR (day-specific entry, if present).
.br
\fBb)\fR The number of records created on that day under the staff member's code (or with their name in the text) is counted from \fBquelle.eintraege\fR.
.br
\fBc)\fR If the roster says work (not \fBb\fR = off, target hours > 0) and at most 2 records exist, the day is flagged as anomalous (red).
.br
\fBd)\fR If the roster says off or no target hours are scheduled and at least 1 record exists, the day is likewise flagged as anomalous (violet); in this case the affected records (patient ID, time, type, content) are additionally listed.
.LP
\fB9)\fR For each flagged day, the latest changes to the roster entry (table \fBdp.protok\fR: time, new duty code, user, PC) are additionally displayed.
.LP
\fB10)\fR The results are written per staff member as a table into the HTML file \fB/DATA/Patientendokumente/Dienstplanauffaelligkeiten_<date>.html\fR; file permissions (660) and owner (\fBschade:praxis\fR) are set.
.LP
\fB11)\fR The configuration file is written if necessary.
.LP
\fB12)\fR If the option \fB-autoupd\fR is active, the program's version number is compared with that of the installation source and, if behind, an update is performed.
.SH PRECONDITIONS
\fBHardware\fR: No particular hardware requirement beyond database access.
.br
\fBSoftware\fR: The program is adjusted to an installation of Opensuse >= 42.1, Debian >= 9, Ubuntu >= 16.04, Mint >= 18 or Fedora >= 24 with standard options. System D must be installed. One of the packet managers \fBapt\fR, \fBdnf\fR, \fByum\fR or \fBzypper\fR must be installed. The program '\fBwget\fR' must be installed. MariaDB must be running, and the tables \fBmitarbeiter\fR, \fBwochenplan\fR, \fBdienstplan\fR, \fBdp.protok\fR and \fBquelle.eintraege\fR (from the practice management system) must exist.
